Smoke soared into the sky aboveÂ the luxury Michelangelo hotel in Sandton on Wednesday as a fire broke out in the kitchen of a nearby eatery. It was quickly contained, said Johannesburg emergency services spokesperson Nana Radebe. "It took us five minutes to extinguish the fire." Radebe said parts of a kitchen caught fire. Michelangelo staff said guests were evacuated as a precaution and no one was injured or hotel property damaged.